AI Subscription & Auto‑Debit Intelligence System – Project Workflow & Task Allocation
Dear [Mentor Name],
Below is the summarized workflow for our project along with the division of responsibilities between the two team members.

Project Development Flow (Start → End)
Phase 1 — Setup (Both Members)

Create GitHub repository
Finalize folder structure
Assign responsibilities (Person A & Person B)
Decide to use a synthetic dataset


Phase 2 — Synthetic Dataset Generation (Person A)

Create synthetic transaction data using Python/Faker
Fields: CustomerID, Date, Merchant, Description, Amount, Balance, SubscriptionFlag
Export as data/final_dataset.csv


Phase 3 — Subscription Detection (Person A)

Clean and normalize transaction descriptions
Identify subscription transactions using keyword rules or simple TF‑IDF classifier
Add: subscription_flag, merchant_cleaned


Phase 4 — Recurring Pattern Detection (Person A)

Detect recurring monthly/weekly patterns
Compute:

frequency
next_expected_date


Update final_dataset.csv with all enriched columns
Upload final dataset to GitHub


Phase 5 — ML Predictions (Person B)
(Work begins after Person A uploads the final dataset)

Predict next debit amount using Linear Regression (scikit‑learn)
Predict next debit date using frequency-based rules


Phase 6 — Risk Prediction (Person B)

Implement BRD‑aligned risk scoring:
risk_score = next_amount / (balance + next_amount)


Categorize risks into High, Medium, Low
Add failure reasons (e.g., low balance)


Phase 7 — Alert Generation (Person B)

Implement template-based alert generation (since GenAI APIs are not allowed)
Format alerts including merchant, amount, days to debit, and recommended action


Phase 8 — Dashboard Development (Person B)

Build Streamlit dashboard displaying:

Active subscriptions
Upcoming debit predictions
Risk scores
Alerts
Monthly spend insights and charts




Phase 9 — Integration & Testing (Both Members)

Verify correctness of NLP detection, patterns, predictions, risk logic, and dashboard outputs
Ensure smooth end‑to‑end flow


Phase 10 — Documentation & Demo (Both Members)

Person A presents data generation, NLP, and pattern detection components
Person B presents ML, risk scoring, alerts, and the dashboard
Upload supporting files to /docs/


Team Responsibilities Summary
Person A — Data, NLP, Pattern Detection

Generate synthetic dataset
Preprocess text
Detect subscription transactions
Identify recurring patterns
Provide enriched dataset (final_dataset.csv)

Person B — ML, Risk, Alerts, Dashboard

Build amount and date prediction logic
Implement risk scoring model
Create alert generation module
Develop end‑to‑end Streamlit dashboard
Integrate all components for final demo


Please let us know if you would like any changes or additional details.
Thanks & Regards,
[Your Name]
